laboratory_examinations.findings: Severe hypoplasia of the anterior pituitary and corpus callosum, with decreased white matter bulk.
Subnormal GH and cortisol responses were noted in four of five children; peak GH of 2.3 ng/L (6.8 mU/L) in one child, and peak cortisol responses varied.
Suboptimal cortisol response was seen in one of three patients tested.
Low IGF-I concentration was observed in all six children.
Moderate testosterone responses to HCG were noted; peak testosterone levels were 5.48 nmol/L (1.58 g/L) after 3 d, and 13.10 nmol/L (3.74 g/L) after 3 wk.
